Legs (
Fig. 1E
). Apically curved spur on each mid and hind outer comb, inner comb with small, blunt spur barely extending beyond longest comb teeth. LR1 2.0–2.2, LR2 0.60–0.65, LR3 0.83–0.88. BV1 1.7–1.8, BV2 3.2– 3.5, BV3 2.5–2.7. SV1 1.25–1.3, SV2 3.3–3.6, SV3 2.46–2.5.

Hypopygium (
Figs 1F, 1H
). TIX bare; anal point parallel-sided, with bluntly tapered apex. SVo (
Fig. 1H
) ca. 50–60 µm, with 2 inner setae, 15–22 long, bases 5–12 µm apart, each arising from tubercle; 3rd very fine seta, 10 long, present in some specimens either between, or distal to strong inner setae. Mvo stem ca. 30 µm, with 20–30 split semi-taeniate and simple setae. Gcx 113–160, Gst 96–108.

Abdomen (

Fig. 5 
A

). Tergites II–VI with spinule patches laterally not reaching apophyses, and not extending to pleurae, narrower anteriorly than posteriorly; on VII and VIII spinule patches quite dense in anterior broad transverse band of spinules. Tergite II with row of 15–20 hooks extending 20–22% of tergite width. Pedes spurii B moderately developed. Pleural fringe on segments III–VIII. Posterolateral ‘comb’ on VIII with 10–14 teeth of relatively uniform size (
Fig. 4H
).
